cs.ET, cs.RO, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper describes the use of a Belousov-Zhabotinsky (BZ) reaction to create a photosensor using liquid marbles. This involves the manipulation of a liquid droplet coated with a hydrophobic powder, which is relevant to the field of soft robotics (cs.RO). The use of electrodes to record potential differences and the analysis of the recorded activity is relevant to the field of unconventional computing (cs.CC). The application of the photosensor in liquid electronics and soft robotics also falls under the category of cyber-physical systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of the BZ reaction to create a responsive material is relevant to the field of neural networks (cs.NE).
